    public interface FixedSizeQueueInterface<E>
extends java.util.Queue<E>

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int getQueueCapacity()
      This method will obtain the maximum size for the queue, namely the number of elements that can be held on the queue without it overflowing.
      int getRemainingQueueSpace()
      This method will return the remaining queue space, or the number of elements that can be added to the queue without it overflowing.
      boolean isQueueFull()
      This method will indicate whether the given queue is full or not.

        int getQueueCapacity()
        This method will obtain the maximum size for the queue, namely the number of elements that can be held on the queue without it overflowing.
